				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Terror Town RPG" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Terror Town RPG is a simple solo game wherein all rules of gameplay are included in a single character sheet. In the game, the player takes the role of a person trapped in the evil Terror Town, a ghost town whose legend claims a corrupt mayor sacrificed the souls of his entire town in order to gain power and eternal life in a dark dimension of pure evil. Now, the town exists in three different worlds at once: Our World, Grey World, and Dark World. In our world, you will find weapons and other useful items. In Dark World, you will find twisted monsters out to kill you. In Grey World, you will find both. Can you survive the survival horror challenge of Terror Town? Will you escape the doomed town, defeat it&amp;rsquo;s diabolical mayor, or just end up falling victim to it&amp;rsquo;s many monsters? The answer awaits you... in Terror Town.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Despite its name, Terror Town RPG is not a role-playing game.  The procedural, solitaire game is played in a series of turns, each turn presenting a challenge to overcome.  If successful, a random die roll determines what the next turn will bring.  The player starts with two pools of points - Escape and Life - which vary during play.  Escape points are used to avoid certain situations; Life points are depleted by failure.  If Life ever reaches zero, the game is lost - otherwise the game ends in success when the player escapes Terror Town.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The print-and-play game rules are presented in tiny typeface on a single page of paper; three pages of cut-out tokens also are provided.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
